    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor Description
      Airplane()
      Default constructor for objects of class Airplane with the random values as default values, except the ID that is 'X' It assigns a random fuel between [MIN_FUEL,1000), a random altitude between [MIN_ALTITUDE,1000), a random x-pos between [X_WEST_BORDER,X_EAST_BORDER], a random y-pos between [Y_NORTH_BORDER,Y_SOUTH_BORDER], a random x-speed between [MIN_X_SPEED,MAX_X_SPEED], and a random y-pos between [MIN_Y_SPEED,MAX_Y_SPEED]
      Airplane​(char ID)
      Constructor for objects of class Airplane that allows the user to change the ID and the rest of the fields are random as the default constructor
      Airplane​(char ID, double fuel, double altitude, int xPos, int yPos, int xSpeed, int ySpeed)
      Constructor for objects of class Airplane that allows the user to set the values for all the fields

      • turnsRequiredToReachColumn

        public int turnsRequiredToReachColumn​(int desiredColumn)
        Returns the number of turns required to move the Airplane to a desired column from its current xPos and xSpeed. Trows an error message when it is imposible to go to the desired column.
        Parameters:
        int - contains the value of the desired column. Throws an exception if the desiredCloumn is not valid
        Returns:
        int containing the number of turns the airplane has to do. Returns 0 if xPos==desiredColumn

      • fly

        public boolean fly()
        The airplane flies to a new x-coordinate and new y-coordinate depending on the the x-speed and the y-speed -If either the x or y coordinate is in the border of the gameboard, the coordinate will not updated
        Returns:
        boolean true if there is enough fuel and the position is updated, it reduces its amount in 1.0 unit.
